Reviewed `src/blog/people/drafts/Jerry-Seinfeld.md` and appended a `FRESH EYES REVIEW` block at the bottom.

**Two biggest flags:**

1. **Bee Movie is missing entirely.** It's the structural twin of Unfrosted (years of obsessive solo work, breakfast-adjacent passion project, mixed reception) but happens 17 years earlier. The draft climaxes on Unfrosted as a first-time risk; with Bee Movie in view, it's the second time he's run the play — much stronger 5w6 evidence.

2. **Shoshanna Lonstein controversy is unmentioned.** The "year he walked off-script" section engages Duke, Unfrosted reviews, and the extreme-left walkback but skips the 1993–1997 relationship that's been the most durable critic-pressure point on him. Combined with the lightly-told Jessica-Sklar timeline, the draft sidesteps the two big personal-life controversies a reader expects to see addressed.

Smaller notes cover the 1998→2024 gap, the "Five logic" / "sealed room" repetition, the Three-vs-Five contrast appearing twice, and structural suggestions to lead with the diagonal-stripe anecdote.
